  <biospec_descr>
    <textblock>
      Head-and-neck cancer patients will undergo a therapeutic lymph node dissection of the
      cervical nodes. This treatment is given whether the patient is enrolled in the study or not.
      Histological specimens of cancer patients are always stored for possible future refference in
      the routine clinical practice.
    </textblock>
  </biospec_descr>
